-- NBA’s New York Knicks Sign Kenyon Martin for Remainder of Season
-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 2013-03-16T04:00:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-15/nba-s-new-york-knicks-sign-kenyon-martin-for-remainder-of-season.html
The New York Knicks, who are
missing injured front-court players Carmelo Anthony,  Tyson Chandler  and Amar’e Stoudemire, signed power forward Kenyon Martin for the rest of the regular season.  Martin, 35, has played in six games since signing the first
of two 10-day contracts on Feb. 23, the Knicks said yesterday in
an e-mailed release.  Martin is in his 13th National Basketball Association
season.  The Knicks have lost the first three games of a five-game
road trip that continues tomorrow at the  Los Angeles Clippers .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rob Gloster in San Francisco at 
